If there are changes in how the client appears to have been feeling, document the changing phases with changing tense. Examples:

> "I was feeling really anxious about <xxx>. I'm feeling a little better now, after we talked about <yyy>."

> "At the beginning of the conversation we were talking a lot about my weight but then we started talking more about exercise and how I'd like to move better. Then we worked on ..."

Be careful not to over-interpret. Remember you are the therapist imagining you are the client, so you don't have direct access to the client's thoughts and feelings. We just need to describe what we can based on what the client actually said.

